You are developing the JYC project itself (bootstrapping).

## Repository
The JYC git repository should be at: ./jyc/
If not yet cloned: git clone https://github.com/kingye/jyc.git
You can use HTTP/HTTPS proxy if required: proxy.sha.sap.corp:8080
Environment variable GH_TOKEN should be set if you need to push branches or create PRs on GitHub.

## Git Rules
- NEVER run `git config user.name` or `git config user.email` (local or global). The git identity is pre-configured by the container. Setting it locally will cause wrong author on commits.
- NEVER run `git config --global` for any setting. Global config is managed by the container startup script.

## Development Workflow
- Always create a feature branch: git checkout -b feat/<name>
- After changes, run tests: cd jyc && cargo test
- Commit with clear messages describing what changed and why
- Push immediately after committing (do not leave unpushed commits)
- Push and create PR when instructed

## Build Environment
- The source is bind-mounted from the host (macOS) into the container (Linux)
- CARGO_TARGET_DIR is set to /tmp/jyc-target to avoid cross-platform conflicts with the host's target/ directory
- Do NOT build into ./target/ directly — always use the CARGO_TARGET_DIR environment variable (already set)
- Rust is NOT pre-installed in the container to keep the image small. Install it on-demand before building (see below).

## Install Rust (first time only)
If `cargo` is not available, install the Rust toolchain:
```bash
curl --proto '=https' --tlsv1.2 -sSf https://sh.rustup.rs | sh -s -- -y
source "$HOME/.cargo/env"
```
This takes ~30 seconds. The toolchain persists until the container is rebuilt.

## Build (when instructed)
1. Ensure Rust is installed (see above)
2. cd jyc && cargo test
3. cargo build --release
4. $CARGO_TARGET_DIR/release/jyc --version
5. Report: version, binary size, test results

## Deploy (when instructed)
1. Verify $CARGO_TARGET_DIR/release/jyc exists
2. Reply to confirm deployment is starting
3. cp $CARGO_TARGET_DIR/release/jyc /usr/local/bin/jyc
4. s6-svc -r /run/service/jyc
Note: JYC will restart. A startup health check email confirms readiness.

## Build and Deploy (when instructed)
Run Build steps, then Deploy steps in sequence.

